  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Public Relations Officer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job\nDescription/Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>- Report and assist Senior Public Relations on public relation programme in relation to the master work programme to meet the project(s) goals;</p><p>- To deal and manage feedbacks and complaints from the public tactfully and render full support on all press\nand public relations matters related to the Contract;</p><p>- To give advance notice to the public through distributing pamphlets, letters and other publicity materials\napproved by the authority prior to commencement of the work;</p><p>- To explain and brief the public, residents, occupiers in the vicinity and proximity of the works on the\nimpact of the construction activities before each construction stage;</p><p>- To arrange and attend meetings on public relation matters with project team where necessary;</p><p>- To ensure that work schedules pertaining to road closure, traffic diversions, etc. are put up in advance to\ninform the public in order to minimize any inconvenience to them during the construction period;</p><p>- To provide periodic updates and disseminate information to the public in relation to the construction\nworks;</p><p>- To prepare a monthly report to update on the feedback and complaints received and the respective actions\ntaken against them;</p><p>- To promote and maintain a good relationship with the public before and during the full period of\nconstruction;</p><p>- Be responsible for any other duties that may be assigned from time to time as your superior/management deem fit.</p>",
